            ```
        *   Alternatively, if `l.f()` returns `android.os.Handler`, hooking `android.os.Handler.post` or `android.os.Handler.dispatchMessage` could catch all UI-bound tasks, regardless of their origin.
    *   **Observing Synchronous Tasks**: Similarly, `Q.d.b.execute` can be hooked to intercept tasks executed immediately.
        *   **Frida Example (Hooking `Q.d.b.execute`):**
            ```javascript
